text:
As for that day, let it be darkness;
    let God above not regard it;
    and let not light shine upon it.

Let darkness and the shadow of death claim it;
    let a cloud settle on it;
    let the blackness of the day terrify it.

As for that night, let darkness capture it;
    let it not rejoice among the days of the year;
    let it not come into the number of the months.

Let its morning stars be dark;
    let it look for light, but have none;
    let it not see the rays of dawn,

For the arrows of the Almighty are within me;
    my spirit drinks in their poison;
    the terrors of God are arrayed against me.

Then I would still have comfort;
    I would revel in pain; it will not subside,
    for I have not concealed the words of the Holy One.

“Therefore, I will not restrain my mouth;
    I will speak in the anguish of my spirit;
    I will complain in the bitterness of my soul.

if you were pure and upright,
    surely now He would rouse Himself on your behalf,
    and He would prosper your righteous dwelling.

“Though I were perfect,
    I would not know myself;
    I would despise my life.

“My soul loathes my life;
    I will freely give my complaint,
    I will speak in the bitterness of my soul.

If I am wicked, woe unto me;
    and if I am righteous, yet will I not lift up my head.
I am full of shame;
    look at my affliction!

a land of darkness, as darkness itself;
    and of the shadow of death, without any order,
    and where the light is as thick darkness.”

You will trust because there is hope;
    yes, you will search about you,
    and you will look around and rest in safety.

But I have understanding as well as you;
    I am not inferior to you.
    Yes, who does not know such things as these?

“I am a laughingstock to my neighbor,
    who calls upon God, and He answers him;
    the righteous, upright man is a laughingstock.

You put my feet in the stocks
    and watch closely all my paths;
    You draw a line around the soles of my feet.

Seeing his days are determined,
    the number of his months are with You;
    You have appointed his bounds that he cannot pass;

“For there is hope for a tree,
    if it is cut down, that it will sprout again,
    and that its tender shoots will not cease.

so man lies down and does not rise;
    until the heavens are no more, he will not awake,
    nor be raised out of his sleep.

The waters wear away the stones;
    its overflow washes away the dust of the earth;
    and You destroy the hope of man.

He will not depart out of darkness;
    the flame will dry out his branches,
    and by the breath of His mouth he will go away.

He has torn me in His wrath, and He has carried a grudge against me.
    He has gnashed me with His teeth;
    my enemy sharpens His gaze upon me.

They have gaped upon me with their mouth;
    they have struck me upon the cheek with reproach;
    they have gathered themselves together against me.

His archers surround me;
He splits open my kidneys and does not pity;
    He pours out my gall upon the ground.

His troops come together
    and build up their road against me;
    they set up camp all around my tent.

Those who dwell in my house, and my maidservants,
    count me for a stranger;
    I am a foreigner in their sight.

be afraid of the sword for yourselves;
    for wrath brings the punishments of the sword,
    that you may know there is a judgment.”

He has swallowed down riches,
    and he will vomit them up again;
    God will cast them out of his belly.

It is drawn and comes out of the body;
    yes, the glittering point comes out of his gall.
Terrors are upon him.

Total darkness is stored up for his treasures.
An unfanned fire will consume him;
    what is left in his tent will be consumed.

The clods of the valley will be sweet unto him;
    and everyone will follow him,
    as countless have gone before.

Men groan from outside the city,
    and the soul of the wounded cries out;
    yet God does not charge them with wrong.

“They are those who rebel against the light;
    they do not know its ways
    nor abide in its paths.

Also the eye of the adulterer waits for the twilight,
    saying, ‘No eye will see me’;
    and he disguises his face.

In the dark they break into houses,
    which they had marked for themselves in the daytime;
    they do not know the light.

For the morning is the same to them as the shadow of death;
    if someone recognizes them,
    they are in the terrors of the shadow of death.

The womb will forget him;
    the worm will feed sweetly on him;
he will be remembered no more,
    and wickedness will be broken like a tree.

They are exalted for a little while but are gone and brought low;
    they are taken out of the way like all others
    and cut off as the tops of the grain.

He breaks open a shaft away from the inhabitants;
    in places forgotten by feet
    they hang far away from men; and they totter.

To man He said:
    ‘Look, the fear of the Lord, that is wisdom;
    And to depart from evil is understanding.’ ”

For want and famine
    they gnawed the parched land;
    fleeing into the wilderness in former time, desolate and waste.

At my right hand their brood arises;
    they push away my feet,
    and they raise against me their ways of destruction.

They tear apart my path,
    they promote my calamity;
    they have no helper.

Terrors are turned on me;
    they pursue my dignity like the wind,
    and my help passes away as a cloud.

let thistles grow instead of wheat,
    and weeds instead of barley.”
The words of Job are ended.

Indeed, I waited for your words;
    I listened to your reasons,
while you searched out what to say.

Yes, I paid attention to you;
and surely none of you convinced Job
    or answered his words.

then He is gracious to him, and says,
    ‘Deliver him from going down to the pit;
    I have found a ransom.’

For he adds rebellion unto his sin;
    he claps his hands among us,
    and multiplies his words against God.”

He does not withdraw His eyes from the righteous;
    but they are on the throne with kings,
    for He establishes them forever, and they are exalted.

“Even so He would have removed you out of distress
    into a broad place where there is no restraint;
    and that which was set on your table would be full of richness.

Concerning the Almighty, we cannot find Him out;
    He is excellent in power, and in judgment,
    and in much righteousness He will not oppress.

Prepare yourself like a man;
    for I will question you,
    and you shall answer Me.

She is hardened against her young ones,
    as though they were not hers;
    her labor is in vain, without concern,

At the sound of the trumpet he says, ‘Aha’;
    he smells the battle afar off,
    the thunder of the captains, and the shouting.

“Prepare yourself now like a man;
    I will question you,
    and you will answer Me.

“Look now at the behemoth
    which I made along with you;
    he eats grass like an ox.

“ ‘Hear, and I will speak;
    I will question you,
    and you declare to Me.’
